Researchers found 14 different strains of TB bacteria in mummies found in the crypt of a church in Vác, Hungary . 
  The mummies were discovered during restoration work at the Dominican church . 
  Mummified remains found to have been infected with tuberculosis . 
  Researchers traced the strains back to a single source in the late Roman period . 
  They found the mummies had been infected by multiple strains of the disease . 
  The remains were found in a crypt at the church in the city of Vác . 
  Researchers say the strains all evolved from a single strain of TB . 
 